Xpath
Xpath is definded as XML path it is a syntax or language for finding any element on the website
Xpath is unique way of finding elements on HTML page


Why need the xpath ?
 I can build my own custom locators based on certain syntax


 1 absulote Xpath
    Start with single /
     it starts looking for elements from parent to child


     Index

     if i have same tagName and i want to point specific element, i can use index, which is [indexNumber]


     /html/body/div/div/[2]/div/div/div[3]

2 Relative Xpath
 start with double // and looks element ANYWHERE on the page
 // li/a --> find all li element in the page




// button[@onclick='button1()']

//button[text()='Button']   ---> Visible text

//button[contains(text(),'ton 1')]
//a[contains(text(),'Dynamic')]

Formula
//TagName[starts-with(@Attribute,'value')]

//TagName[@attribute='value']
[1] - > index

//*[@name='button1')]

//button[end-with(@id,'button1')]

//button[contains(@id,'button')]

